Squeeze the @Steamed Brown Basmati Rice{1%pouch} to separate the grains. Tear a strip approx 2cm along the top.

Cook the rice according to pack instructions. Set aside until serving.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced).

Halve the @bell pepper{1}(halved) and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips, then chop into roughly 1cm pieces.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Put the @cornflour{10%g} into a #large bowl{} and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Add the @diced British chicken thigh{240%g} and toss to coat completely in the cornflour.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the chopped pepper and onion. Stir-fry until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the garlic and cook for ~{30%seconds}. Transfer to a #medium bowl{} and set aside for now.

Pop your (now empty) #frying pan{} back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once hot, add the chicken and fry until golden brown, ~{6-8%minutes} total. Turn every 2-3 mins.

Once the chicken has browned, lower the heat to medium and return the cooked veg to the pan.

Add the @ketjap manis{50%g}, @rice vinegar{30%ml}, @tomato ketchup{2%tbsp}, @sugar{3/4%tsp} and @water{75%ml} to the pan.

> See pantry for all three amounts of ketjap manis, rice vinegar and ketchup.

Stir to combine and simmer until the sauce has reduced slightly and the chicken is cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed. Remove from the heat.

> TIP: The sauce should be sticky, but add a splash more water if you'd like.

Spoon the rice into your #bowls{}.

Serve with the sticky chicken and veg on top.

Enjoy!